<p>The state's primary utility provider, Pacific Gas & Electric (PG&E), along with Southern California Edison and San Diego Gas & Electric, serves millions of customers across diverse climate zones. From the coastal regions with their mild temperatures to the inland valleys with more extreme seasonal variations, California's geography creates unique opportunities for both solar energy harvesting and efficient HVAC system design. The state's commitment to renewable energy, evidenced by its ambitious clean energy goals and robust incentive programs, makes it an ideal environment for homeowners looking to reduce their carbon footprint while achieving substantial long-term savings.</p>

