<h2>California Incentives & Rebates</h2>

<p>California offers one of the most comprehensive renewable energy incentive packages in the United States, making solar and efficient HVAC systems highly accessible to homeowners across all income levels.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Federal Solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC):</strong> The 30% federal tax credit applies to the total installed cost of solar systems, including equipment, installation, and related electrical work. This credit can be claimed against federal income taxes owed and can be carried forward to future tax years if the credit exceeds current year tax liability. For a typical \$25,000 solar installation, this represents \$7,500 in direct tax savings.</li>

<li><strong>Self-Generation Incentive Program (SGIP):</strong> California's SGIP provides rebates up to \$1,000 per kWh for battery storage systems, with enhanced incentives for low-income households and those in high-fire-risk areas. The program specifically targets energy storage paired with solar systems, helping homeowners achieve energy independence and grid resilience. Rebate levels are tiered based on available funding, making early application advantageous.</li>

<li><strong>PG&E Energy Savings Assistance Program:</strong> Income-qualified customers can receive free energy efficiency upgrades including HVAC system replacements, weatherization, and energy-efficient appliances. The program serves households earning up to 250% of federal poverty guidelines and can provide thousands of dollars in free improvements.</li>

<li><strong>Local Utility Rebates:</strong> Major California utilities offer various rebates for energy-efficient HVAC systems, smart thermostats, and solar installations. Southern California Edison provides rebates up to \$3,500 for high-efficiency heat pumps, while San Diego Gas & Electric offers similar programs with rebates varying by system efficiency rating.</li>

<li><strong>Property Tax Exemption:</strong> California's solar property tax exclusion prevents the added value of solar installations from increasing property tax assessments, providing ongoing savings throughout the system's lifetime. This benefit can save homeowners hundreds of dollars annually in property taxes.</li>
</ul>

